<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1856" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1856">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.3111/40.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Venezuelan Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Venezuelan Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Atlantic City, New Jersey</hi></placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-26">June 26,
                                    1914</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>It becomes my duty to inform your excellency that Senor Rojas, Minister
                            of Venezuela, died today in this city and that in my capacity as
                            Secretary of the Legation, I have taken charge as Chargé d’Affaires ad
                            interim.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Luis Churion</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>